{"article_id":"DwdfykyumnY9fjQ0","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"With the threats billowing out of North Korean dictator Kim Jong Un 's regime at an unusually rapid clip ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"concern is mounting","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"that the young leader could be backing himself into a corner","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"-- feeling compelled to do something","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"or lose face .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Shortly after midnight local time , North Korean state television reported","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"that Kim signed orders","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"to put the nation 's rockets on combat-ready status .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"In a photo","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"released on state-run media ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"a chart","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"titled `` U.S. mainland strike plan ''","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"could be seen","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"and a map showed missiles","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"arcing into Hawaii , Washington , Los Angeles and Austin , Texas .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"The Pentagon is worried","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"Kim may put himself in a position","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"where he feels","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"he has to act on his threats .","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"The North Koreans ,","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"while having made progress in their ballistic missile program ,","depth":14},{"id":21,"text":"still have not mastered the technology","depth":15},{"id":22,"text":"of delivering a nuclear device by a long-range missile .","depth":15},{"id":23,"text":"But they are making progress ,","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"and that is what has the Pentagon concerned .","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"Plus there is the concern","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"that North Korea could strike at South Korea , a top U.S. ally .","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"`` The North Koreans seem to be headed in a different direction here .","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"So we will unequivocally defend","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"and we are unequivocally committed to that alliance with South Korea , as well as our other allies in that region of the world .","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"And we will be prepared --","depth":15},{"id":31,"text":"we have to be prepared","depth":15},{"id":32,"text":"to deal with any eventuality there , ''","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"Defense Secretary Chuck Hagel said Thursday .","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"Kim warned Friday","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"he is preparing to `` settle accounts with the U.S. ''","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"after the U.S. deployed B-2 stealth bombers to South Korea","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"to participate in a training exercise Thursday .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"The third-generation dictator 's comments in a meeting with senior generals are part of a rising tide of threats","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"meant to highlight anger over the drills and recent U.N. sanctions over Pyongyang 's nuclear test .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"State media says","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"Kim signed a rocket preparation plan","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"and ordered rockets on standby","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"to strike the U.S. mainland , South Korea , Guam and Hawaii .","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Later Friday at the main square in Pyongyang , tens of thousands of North Koreans turned out for a 90-minute mass rally in support of Kim 's call to arms .","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"Men and women , many of them in olive drab uniforms , stood in arrow-straight lines ,","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"fists raised","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"as they chanted ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"`` Death to the U.S . imperialists . ''","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"Placards in the plaza bore harsh words for South Korea as well ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"including , `` Let 's rip the puppet traitors to death ! ''","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"The U.S. military says","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"the two B-2 stealth bombers","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"sent to South Korea","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"were meant to demonstrate the Pentagon 's commitment","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"to defend its ally against threats from North Korea .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"The two B-2 Spirit bombers flew more than 6,500 miles from Whiteman Air Force Base in Missouri to South Korea ,","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"dropping inert munitions","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"before returning to the U.S. ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"according to a statement","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"released by U.S . Forces Korea .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"`` The United States is steadfast in its alliance commitment to the defense of the Republic of Korea ,","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"to deterring aggression ,","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"and to ensuring peace and stability in the region , ''","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"the statement said .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"The B-2 Spirit is capable of delivering both conventional and nuclear weapons .","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"The Pentagon said","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"the mission was part of its ongoing Foal Eagle training exercise series ,","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"which began March 1","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"and ends April 30 .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"Hagel said Thursday afternoon","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"that the move was part of normal exercises","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"and not intended to provoke a reaction from North Korea .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"The exercise , though , was announced a day after North Korea said","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"it had shut down a key military hotline","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"usually used","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"to arrange passage for workers and goods through the Demilitarized Zone .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"North Korea ,","depth":5},{"id":78,"text":"which says","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"it considers the U.S.-South Korean military drills preparations for invasion ,","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"has pumped out a string of threats in state media .","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"In the most dramatic case , Pyongyang made the highly improbable vow","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"to nuke the United States .","depth":5},{"id":83,"text":"On Friday , state media released a photo of Kim and his senior generals","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"huddled in front of a map","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"showing routes for envisioned strikes against cities on both American coasts .","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"Experts believe","depth":5},{"id":87,"text":"the country is years away from developing nuclear-tipped missiles","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"that could strike the United States .","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"Many say","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"they 've also seen no evidence","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"that Pyongyang has long-range missiles","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"that can hit the U.S. mainland .","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"Still , there are fears of a localized conflict , such as a naval skirmish in disputed Yellow Sea waters .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Such naval clashes have happened three times since 1999 .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"There 's also the danger","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"that such a clash could escalate .","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"Seoul has vowed to hit back hard","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"the next time","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"it is attacked .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"North Korea 's threats are also worrisome","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"because of its arsenal of short- and mid-range missiles","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"that can hit targets in South Korea and Japan .","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"Seoul is only a short drive from the heavily armed border","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"separating the Koreas .","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"`` The North can fire 500,000 rounds of artillery on Seoul in the first hour of a conflict , ''","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"analysts Victor Cha and David Kang wrote recently for Foreign Policy magazine .","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"They also note","depth":6},{"id":108,"text":"that North Korea has a history","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"of testing new South Korean leaders ;","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"President Park Geun-hye took office late last month .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"`` Since 1992 , the North has welcomed these five new leaders","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"by disturbing the peace , ''","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"they wrote .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":227,"left":190,"right":226,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":190,"left":164,"right":189,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":118,"right":163,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":0,"right":117,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":117,"left":1,"right":116,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":2,"right":115,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":163,"left":156,"right":162,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":156,"left":152,"right":155,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":127,"right":151,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":120,"right":126,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":5,"right":119,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":119,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":124,"right":125,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":121,"right":123,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":122,"right":12,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":122,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{